The Smart car mimics the flight of the bumblebee 
What would be the best method to develop technologies to avoid collisions, if not the imitation of sensors obstacles in nature? 
For example, the bumble bees. 
In a surprising draft presented at the CEATEC Japan, the bees were the starting point for Nissan's engineers to design the next generation of the system for prevention of collisions. 
The Nissan, in cooperation with the University of Tokyo, designed the guidance system of robotic cars BR23C rate imitator of nature, which gave him the characteristics of the bees, with the ultimate goal of creating a system that can dodge all the collisions . 
During the flight each bumblebee creates its own particular oval is actually very much like our cap security - explained in the exhibition Kazuhhiro Doi, director of MOP and technological development and research. 
They play an important role in the compound eyes of the bees that are able to see in all directions at an angle greater than 300 degrees. 
To copy the function of the compound eyes, the engineers used the system for measuring the length by laser beam. 
This identifies the obstacles in front of BR23C within a distance of 2 meters at an angle of 180 degrees, calculates its distance and sends a signal to the microprocessor of the vehicle which immediately becomes a maneuver to avoid collision. 
In a fraction of a second identifying the obstacle, then the robot vehicle imitating the movements of the bees, amending the address to the extent required by turning the wheels. 
Unlike any currently existing system, this maneuver is totally instinctive. 
"If not, the robot vehicle could not react quickly enough to dodge obstacles" - explains Toshiyuki Andoh, head of the Laboratory for Mobility and the draft of the robot vehicles. 
Should react immediately and instinctively, as this technology is for the most vulnerable inner layer of the protective cap security, in a layer inside of which are currently considered inevitable all types of collisions. 
The whole process should reflect what makes a bumblebee to dodge other bees. 
This process must be conducted in an open and close your eyes. 
However, unlike the bees, the movement can not go up, down or diagonally, but can only be two-dimensional and only in the direction of rotation of the wheels 
In this way, instead of the infinite possibilities that exist for the bees to dodge other bees, used here only as a possibility for the robot movement of the car rolling and accelerated further slowing. 
The BR23C uses lithium-polymer batteries that are lighter and more energy density, meaning they have a life span longer than the lithium-ion. 
According to Andoh, the important thing is the instinctive reaction and intelligent and not the processing capacity of the data, let alone the storage. 
This device on every second only to process some input signals and respond as appropriate. 
There is no need to store this data or to react instinctively with a logic based on data from previous exercises, and uses only a few tens of kilobytes of memory. 
There was no need gigabytes of memories, or megabytes. 
This is the first step to develop the technology to immediately dodge obstacles, which according to calculations by Nissan, in ten years can be incorporated into the models produced in series. 
Another possibility for implementation is to incorporate the unit into a navigation system for GPS satellite for the driver to his destination, avoiding obstacles in its path. 
