In August 2008 the domestic prices of industrial sales grew by 0.1 per cent compared with prices last month and a 12.9 per cent compared with prices in the month of August 2007 - reported The Central Bureau of Statistics (ksh). 
The prices of industrial exports rose to 1.1 per cent compared to July of 2008 and decreased 3.9 percent from the previous year. 
And as a result of changes in domestic prices and export prices of industrial production grew 0.7 percent from the previous month and by 3.2 percent over the previous year. 
The prices of industrial sales rose by only a minimal extent, with a 0.1 per cent. 
The sales prices of the domestic sectors of the processing industry rose slightly, with a 0.1 per cent compared to July. 
The largest increase in the magnitude of prices occurred in August 2008, in the field of production of leather and footwear (2.8 percent) due primarily to increased by 4.6 percent month on Bags and belts and increased by 2.5 per cent of the footwear. 
The higher level of prices of basic plastic materials and chemicals has resulted in a significant increase in monthly prices of the industry in the chemical materials (1.6 percent). 
There was a decline in prices in the petrochemical sector (1.4 percent), in the production of electrical machinery and instruments (0.9 percent) and - at a minimum extent - in the fields of timber processing (0.1 percent). 
Did not change the prices of paper, the editorials and that of printers. 
In the other sectors of the processing industry registered a price rise between 0.2 and 0.9 per cent. 
In the electricity, gas, heat and water that represent a significant weight within the domestic trade, was recorded in the month of August, an increase of 0.3 percent, primarily as a result of the effect of rising prices Officers from the first of July. 
In a comparison of a twelve-month period - in domestic sales of the industrial processing, the largest price increase was recorded in the petrochemical sector (32.4 percent). 
In the processing sector of the metal showed an increase of 13.2 percent, while in the food industry, beverages and tobacco, weight determinant, there was an increase of 11 percent. 
There was a decline in prices in the textile industry (2.5 percent) and in the manufacture of electrical machinery and instruments (0.3 percent). 
In the rest of the sectors processors pace of price growth was between 0.6 and 9.1 per cent. 
During the past year in the processing industry with overall prices rose 10.2 percent. 
The prices of electric power, gas, heat and water exceeded 18.7 percent the previous year's prices. 
In August, between the various sectors of the domestic trade of the largest monthly increase in prices (0.7 percent) was recorded in the sectors of capital goods. 
In the sectors of consumer goods, prices grew 0.3 percent in the prices of energy and industry sectors intermediaries there was no change with respect to the previous month. 
In August 2008, compared with the same month last year, the largest price increase occurred in the energy sectors in industry and intermediate (16.8 percent). 
In the branches producing consumer goods saw a decline of 6.8 percent and capital goods by 1.4 percent. 
Export prices in the industry estimated at HUF increased by 1.1 percent from the previous month, and compared to 12 months, there was a decrease of 3.9 per cent. 
The contribution of our national currency in one month fell to 1.7 per cent against the euro and 7.1 percent against the dollar, compared to August 2007 strengthened by 7.5 percent compared with to the euro and 15.9 percent against the dollar. 
